  "id": "305473f5-1982-5789-a33e-2dd8989c8d4d",
  "slug": "how-to-make-home-made-siopao-asado-recipe",
  "name": "Siopao Asado Recipe",
  "recipe_type": "dessert",
  "brief_description": "Steamed hot buns with a sweet meaty filling. Siopao asado can be enjoyed anytime.&nbsp;",
  "cuisine": "Filipino",
  "instructions": [
    {
      "position": 1,
      "text": "Cook the Asado filling by heating the shortening in a pan"
    },
    {
      "position": 2,
      "text": "Saute the garlic and onions"
    },
    {
      "position": 3,
      "text": "Put-in the pork and cook until the color of the outer part turns light brown"
    },
    {
      "position": 4,
      "text": "Add the soy sauce, oyster sauce, hoisin sauce, and sugar then mix well. Simmer for 5&nbsp;minutes."
    },
    {
      "position": 5,
      "text": "Put in the corn starch (diluted in water) and mix until the texture of the sauce becomes&nbsp;thick. Set aside."
    },
    {
      "position": 6,
      "text": "Make the dough by placing warm water in a bowl then add the yeast and sugar and mix well.&nbsp;Leave the mixture for 10 to 15 minutes"
    },
    {
      "position": 7,
      "text": "In a mixing bowl, put-in the flour, baking powder, shortening (or lard), and the yeast-sugar-water mixture then mix well (bubbles should have formed on top by then)."
    },
    {
      "position": 8,
      "text": "Knead the combined mixture until the texture of the dough becomes fine. Let the dough&nbsp;rise by setting it aside for at least an hour (place in the mixing bowl and cover the top )."
    },
    {
      "position": 9,
      "text": "Knead the dough again then cut into individual slices (this will be the dough per&nbsp;individual siopao)."
    },
    {
      "position": 10,
      "text": "Flatten the dough until a round shape is formed using a rolling pin."
    },
    {
      "position": 11,
      "text": "Put the asado filling on the middle of the flattened dough and wrap. (refer to the video for the technique if interested)"
    },
    {
      "position": 12,
      "text": "Place the siopao in a steamer and steam for 15 minutes."
    },
    {
      "position": 13,
      "text": "Serve hot with Panlasang Pinoy Siopao Sauce. Share and enjoy!"
    }
  ],
  "servings": 8,
